<br>
I'd be happy to give my old quested items to the vault once I outgrow them.  I'd even happily give player crafted items to the vault when they lose effectiveness for me.  But I do think it a good idea to leave store bought items out of the vault as they are of a lesser wuality and would only become a drain on guild funds.<br>
<br>
On that note, I have some bear-hide boots and a sveabone hilt sword for the vault right now.<br>
<br>
Duelin (Agravaine) <p><img src="http://members.home.net/geist22/sigs/Agravaine.gif" border="0">


</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#676767><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ucixitheevenstar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cixi The Evenstar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lad/Lass</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#F2CF7E>(10/31/01 4:00:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=81.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Guild Vault</span><hr size=1> I'm not sure this is the right place to put it... hrm.<br>
I'm not sure I should meddle in the affairs of the guilds as merely an applicant.<br>
Hrm... Not being sure never stops he though.<br>
<br>
Yesterday, I met up with Gnab. I had noticed he was in Jordheim for an extended period, and assumed he was doing trades. I quickly found out he's an armourer, and I asked if he was willing to craft me some armor.<br>
In the end, he proposed to sell me his &quot;old&quot; set of enchanted armour at a &quot;good price&quot;. He asked 5gp, and generous (and naive) as I am, I offered him 6 (all I had), since trades are important, and I figured that once my equipment was up to par I didn't need money for some time... hrm.<br>
Later, I found out Gnab could have made 10gp simply by selling his equipment to a vendor. Made me feel somewhat guilty about my &quot;generosity&quot;, when it turned out I somewhat robbed him.<br>
I also noticed that, until now, the armor hasn't become less efficient. Maybe because of the enchantment, maybe because I was lucky. *shrug* Fact is, after I'm &quot;done&quot; with it, I'm sure there's still somebody in the guild who could put it to good use.<br>
<br>
I've noticed that in Midgard, armor and weapons are replaced fairly often (ooc Contrary to Norrath, where a certain enchanter wore his Oracle Robe all the way to 56 without a real impact on his performance). This high turnover rate has a serious effect on the available amount of money we have.<br>
<br>
Therefor i wonder if it would be a good idea to set up a system where things are handed down (for a price) instead of sold back to vendors. I'm not sure on how such a system should work, I'll leave that to smarter people... hrm.<br>
Fact is, the armor I got from Gnab has helped me tremendously, and in a few days, a week at most, I can help another member of Siol Lear the way it helped me. Therefor, I shall consider the 6gp I payed, a rent, and not a purchase. And if Gnab can rent this suit to one or two more people, he might actually make a profit, allowing him to make even better armour in the future.<br>
<br>
hrm... Once again, a chaotic collection of thoughts, despite my attempts to make them as clear as possible. It's the way my Troll brain works I'm afraid.<br>
<br>
Kind regards,<br>
<br>
Grishnok,<br>
Two Ton Thane. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showPrevMessage?topicID=81.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showNextMessage?topicID=81.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=81.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.emailToFriend?topicID=81.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.threadControl?topicID=81.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/traditional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=81.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub5.ezboard.com/ftheclanmaclearfrm9.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=81.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub5.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="theclanmacleargeneral">The Great Hall<option value="theclanmaclearfrm8">Inner Court<option value="theclanmaclearfrm6">Events<option value="theclanmaclearfrm5">Provisioner's Square<option value="theclanmaclearfrm4">Chief's Council Chambers<option value="theclanmaclearfrm7">Senate Chambers<o